Anonymous Fri 08 May 2020 17:31:47 No.30124305 Report
Quoted By:
>>30122342
Reynaerde here. Thanks for the feedback. The whole size difference thing between the two characters has been a stealth challenge in writing the story. There aren't many things I've read in my life that go in depth on it, so somewhat ironically I don't have any giants on whose shoulders to stand. Similarly it can be hard to imagine some of the logistics, and how they would work, because of a similar lack of experience. It's something you don't really think about, but often when I'm writing and describing an action that might or might not be possible, I'll mimic it for myself. Stuff like, if you're sitting in a chair and you've got your jacket draped over the back, how easily can you reach into one of the pockets.

So barring some truly autismal taking of measures and mapping out the size of Franky's world, there is a certain uncertainty that's hard to get rid of. There's also the whole square cube law, meaning she's quite heavy, which I suspect also influences descriptions and the way they're interpreted. And there's also the fact that the way I'm trying to write is to filter it somewhat through Stephen's point of view, rather than giving direct descriptions. Either way, I'll have to keep this in mind. At its heart the story is still

>acquire ginormous tigress

And half the fun for me as the writer is kind of figuring out how it all fits together.
